  "name": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Project requirements for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are documented in the design history file and referenced throughout the credibility argument narrative, though the formal structured binding to those requirement IRIs is handled at the project level outside this Minimal-profile package.",
