      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change <2% between medium and fine mesh; GCI reported.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study (coarse/medium/fine: ~80k, ~240k, ~720k elements) was performed on the screw-rod assembly. The Grid Convergence Index for stiffness QoI was 0.8%, and for yield force was 1.1%, both below the 2% acceptance threshold. Fine mesh adopted for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals converge to <1e-6; Newton-Raphson equilibrium norm <1e-4 for nonlinear steps.",
      "rationale": "The sparse direct solver (SPARSE) was employed for linear steps; Newton-Raphson with line search for nonlinear contact phases. Force residual norm converged to <1e-5 at all load increments. No divergence events recorded across 11 model instances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments completed by a reviewer not involved in model construction.",
      "rationale": "An independent senior simulation engineer reviewed all model setup files, boundary condition definitions, contact pair specifications, and material property assignments. Discrepancies identified during review were corrected prior to production runs. Review records are archived in the design history file."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model with von Mises yield and isotropic hardening accepted for Ti-6Al-4V screw and CoCr rod under quasi-static loading.",
      "rationale": "The constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening, von Mises yield) is well-established for Ti-6Al-4V and CoCr alloys under quasi-static monotonic loading. Strain-rate effects are negligible at ASTM F1717 displacement rates (5 mm/min). Contact interactions at screw-rod and screw-vertebral body block interfaces modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation. Model form uncertainty is bounded by the validation comparison itself."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports for production lot; geometric inputs from CMM-verified CAD; friction coefficients from literature with sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and yield strength for Ti-6Al-4V and CoCr rod were taken from certified material test reports for the production lot used in bench testing. CAD geometry was verified against CMM measurements (mean deviation <0.02 mm). Friction coefficient sensitivity analysis showed <3% QoI variation across the plausible range (0.1–0.3), confirming low sensitivity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test specimens from production-representative lots; CMM inspection confirms dimensional conformance.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested (Lab 1: n=6, Lab 2: n=5). All specimens were drawn from production-representative manufacturing lots and inspected by CMM prior to testing. Dimensional conformance to design nominal was confirmed for all 11 specimens. Sample size exceeds the minimum threshold for the required credibility level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted under at least two independent loading configurations or fixture orientations representative of COU boundary conditions.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration (15-degree offset). While this configuration is the regulatory standard, only one test condition was exercised, preventing assessment of condition-to-condition variability. Achieved level (2) is below the required level (3); this gap is acknowledged and mitigated by the strong cross-laboratory reproducibility observed (CV <4% across labs)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions, geometry, and material inputs demonstrably match test specimen measurements and test fixture configuration.",
      "rationale": "Each of the 11 FEA model instances was individualized using the CMM-measured dimensions of the corresponding test specimen. Fixture geometry (loading blocks, pin locations) was reproduced from engineering drawings verified against lab photographs. Material properties matched to the certified test report for each production lot. Equivalency is formally documented in the V&V plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All QoI differences <10%; E/uval <1.96 for each QoI across all 11 specimens.",
      "rationale": "For stiffness, mean FEA-to-experiment difference was 4.2% (max 8.7%); for yield force 3.8% (max 7.1%); for force at 40 mm 5.1% (max 9.4%). E/uval ratios were 0.81, 0.74, and 0.92 respectively, all below the 1.96 threshold. All acceptance criteria satisfied for all 11 specimens. Comparison methodology followed ASME V&V 40 Section 5.4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly correspond to design performance requirements and regulatory submission endpoints.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs are the exact metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and cited in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. They directly index structural integrity and fatigue precursor behavior. No surrogate or proxy quantities are used; the validation QoIs are identical to the design performance requirements referenced in the project requirements documentation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (geometry, loading, material, boundary conditions) is representative of the intended COU without extrapolation beyond validated domain.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity replicates the COU scenario exactly: same screw geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm), same loading protocol (ASTM F1717 compression-bending), same material system (Ti-6Al-4V screw, CoCr rod, UHMWPE vertebral body blocks). No extrapolation beyond the validated domain is required for the intended regulatory submission use. The validation activities are therefore directly and fully relevant to the COU."
    }
