  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Medium model risk, Medium decision consequence application. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is mitigated by strong cross-laboratory reproducibility (CV <4%) and the regulatory standardization of the ASTM F1717 single-condition protocol. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance criteria (<10% difference, E/uval <1.96) across all 11 specimens. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory use. Project requirements for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are documented in the design history file and were used to define the acceptance bounds applied in the output comparison.",
